<subSubSection id="8081656D9811701B1BB0F9B0FDBCAC8B" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C82436E69811701B1BB0F9B0FDBCAC8B" blockId="6.[151,1437,1660,1975]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">
The new genus 
<taxonomicName id="0F9B4D659811701B1A6CF9B0FE2CADAB" authorityName="Haque &amp; White &amp; Cavanagh &amp; Biswas &amp; Hossain" authorityYear="2021" box="[331,471,1660,1686]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1A6CF9B0FE2CADAB" box="[331,471,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Maculabatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as several new species, was recently assigned to a group of morphologically similar stingray species (
<bibRefCitation id="AC0A4B179811701B1A88F96CFD8BAD87" author="Last, P. R. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V. &amp; Alpermann, T. J." box="[431,624,1696,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" pagination="66 - 78" refId="ref7224" refString="Last, P. R., Bogorodsky, S. V. &amp; Alpermann, T. J. (2016 c) Maculabatis ambigua sp. nov., a new whipray (Myliobatiformes: Dasyatidae) from the Western Indian Ocean. Zootaxa, 4154 (1), 66 - 78. http: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4154.1.4" type="journal article" year="2016">
Last 
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1ACFF96DFDDAAD87" box="[488,545,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">et al.</emphasis>
2016c
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="AC0A4B179811701B195BF96CFC0DAD86" author="Manjaji-Matsumoto, B. M. &amp; Last, P. R." box="[636,1014,1696,1723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" pagination="335 - 353" refId="ref7452" refString="Manjaji-Matsumoto, B. M. &amp; Last, P. R. (2016) Two new whiprays, Maculabatis arabica sp. nov. and M. bineeshi sp. nov. (Myliobatiformes: Dasyatidae), from the northern Indian Ocean. Zootaxa, 4144 (3), 335 - 353. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4144.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Last 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The recently described 
<taxonomicName id="0F9B4D659811701B1E37F96CFF0FADE3" authorityName="Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Last" authorityYear="2016" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bineeshi">
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1E37F96CFF0FADE3" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Maculabatis bineeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="B08C76769811701B1AE1F908FDB2ADE3" box="[454,585,1732,1758]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
for the first time in this study (
<figureCitation id="50A02A639811701B18EDF908FBD4ADE3" box="[970,1071,1732,1758]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,848,872]" captionTargetBox="[163,1421,193,814]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,824]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal and ventral image of Maculabatis bineeshi from Cox’s Bazar (Male, DW= 43.18 cm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448236/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Figure 3</figureCitation>
), with a total of 
<specimenCount id="DE9DFD6F9811701B1E27F908FA67ADE3" box="[1280,1436,1732,1758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" type="generic">21 specimens</specimenCount>
recorded, both morphologically (
<bibRefCitation id="AC0A4B179811701B1934F924FC6DAC3E" author="Manjaji-Matsumoto, B. M. &amp; Last, P. R." box="[531,918,1768,1795]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" pagination="335 - 353" refId="ref7452" refString="Manjaji-Matsumoto, B. M. &amp; Last, P. R. (2016) Two new whiprays, Maculabatis arabica sp. nov. and M. bineeshi sp. nov. (Myliobatiformes: Dasyatidae), from the northern Indian Ocean. Zootaxa, 4144 (3), 335 - 353. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4144.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Last 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and genetically. 
<taxonomicName id="0F9B4D659811701B1F41F925FB1DAC3F" authorityName="Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Last" authorityYear="2016" box="[1126,1254,1768,1794]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arabica">
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1F41F925FB1DAC3F" box="[1126,1254,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">M. arabica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="50A02A639811701B1FDEF924FAA6AC3F" box="[1273,1373,1768,1794]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[467,1120,943,1537]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[457,1130,932,1545]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal image of Maculabatis arabica from Cox’s Bazar (Female, DW= 48.26 cm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448238" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448238/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">Figure 4</figureCitation>
) was genetically identified from 
<specimenCount id="DE9DFD6F9811701B1AEAF8C1FD93AC1B" box="[461,616,1804,1831]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
and morphologically identified from another 
<specimenCount id="DE9DFD6F9811701B1F56F8C0FAF5AC1B" box="[1137,1294,1804,1830]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" type="generic">18 specimens</specimenCount>
. In addition, 
<specimenCount id="DE9DFD6F9811701B1BB0F8FDFEA9AC77" box="[151,338,1840,1867]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" type="generic">seven specimens</specimenCount>
that were morphologically most consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="0F9B4D659811701B1857F8FDFC0EAC77" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[880,1013,1841,1866]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrura">
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1857F8FDFC0EAC77" box="[880,1013,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">M. macrura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were examined. 
<taxonomicName id="0F9B4D659811701B1F94F8FDFAC3AC77" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1203,1336,1841,1866]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrura">
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1F94F8FDFAC3AC77" box="[1203,1336,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">M. macrura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only recently been established as a valid species, and is morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0F9B4D659811701B1F1AF899FA63AC52" authority="(Last et al. 2016 a)" baseAuthorityName="Last" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1085,1432,1876,1903]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gerrardi">
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1F1AF899FB3BAC53" box="[1085,1216,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">M. gerrardi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AC0A4B179811701B1FE8F898FA6BAC52" author="Last, P. &amp; Naylor, G. &amp; Seret, B. &amp; White, W. &amp; de Carvalho, M. &amp; Stehmann, M." box="[1231,1424,1876,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" refId="ref7175" refString="Last, P., Naylor, G., Seret, B., White, W., de Carvalho, M. &amp; Stehmann, M. (2016 a) Rays of the World. CSIRO publishing, Melbourne, ix + 790 pp." type="book" year="2016">
Last 
<emphasis id="FAEFEAF49811701B1E2FF899FABAAC53" box="[1288,1345,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="217">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, with distinguishing characteristics poorly understood. Further genetic studies are therefore recommended to assign these specimens to the correct species.
</paragraph>
